  <thing id="cDthShdAdt" name="Shadow Adept" description="Whenever you cast a shadow conjuration or shadow evocation spell from the death mage spell list (including lower- and higher-level versions of those spells), you may use it to emulate any cleric, bard or sorcerer/wizard spell from the conjuration or evocation (as appropriate) schools. A typical death mage who casts those spells may only use them to emulate sorcerer/wizard spells, as outlined in the spell descriptions in the {i}Pathfinder Roleplaying Game Core Rulebook{/i}." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Emulate cleric or bard spells with shadow conjuration/evocation.">
